# Development Standards

## No Shortcuts

- No wrong enums, skipped migrations, hardcoded IDs, hardcoded amounts, or fake data.
- Use existing services/helpers before creating new ones.
- Sweep `scripts/` before adding scripts; many already exist.
- Work only inside `/Users/andremacbookpro/mymoolah` and subdirectories.
- Never use git worktrees.

## Security

- JWT HS512 with short expiry.
- Parameterized SQL only.
- AES-256-GCM for sensitive data.
- RBAC on privileged actions.
- Structured logs with PII redaction.
- Safe user-facing errors; no stack traces, secrets, SQL, or provider internals.

## Financial Integrity

- ACID transactions for multi-step financial writes.
- Double-entry journals must balance to the cent.
- Use immutable correction journals for historical ledger fixes.
- Get explicit André approval before production writes or destructive changes.

## Definition Of Done

- Clean code and no new linter errors.
- Relevant docs updated.
- Tests added/run proportional to risk.
- Migrations include rollback when applicable.
- Security impact considered.
- Session log and handover updated when work is complete.
